Update from @NYCSanitation Commissioner Grayson: The storm is shaping up to be challenging/potentially dangerous. 2,000 Workers in this pm working through night. 700+ salt spreaders ready. Plows start w/2 inches of snow. Will work methodically to get the streets clear/passable as quickly as is safe.

We ask all New Yorkers to stay off the roads as much as possible. Brining of some streets/bike lanes successfully completed this morning. Alternate Side Parking is suspended Monday, Feb. 1 & Tuesday, Feb. 2. Open Restaurants roadway dining is suspended Monday.

We are expecting to see coronavirus cases in New York City, however we have plans in place to keep everyone safe. We are prepared to identify and contain the spread of this virus. Here's what you need to know:

If you have recently traveled to the Wuhan area, or been in contact with someone who has, and experience: -Fever
-Cough
-Shortness of breath

Get to a doctor IMMEDIATELY.

At this time, we believe coronavirus can only be spread person-to-person through prolonged contact with someone who has it.

New Yorkers — go about your daily lives but remain vigilant for symptoms and take basic hygiene steps. Wash hands frequently, cover your mouth when you cough or sneeze and stay home if you feel sick.

We will continue to monitor the situation and provide updates as needed.

The Rabbit Hole Virtual Whiskey Tasting Experience is the ultimate at-home indulgence, for those who don’t fancy a night-out just yet. Buy tickets to this experience, and you’ll get a tasting kit including two full-size bottles of award-winning Rabbit Hole Whiskey, two 2021 Rabbit Hole Commemorative Derby tasting glasses and a tasting mat sent to your home. Guests will also be provided with a Zoom link to take part in an intimate virtual guided tasting session and virtual tour of the state-of-the-art Rabbit Hole Distillery in Louisville. Whether you’re a whiskey connoisseur or a total novice, this event promises a fascinating (and delicious) night-in! 
.

You can support local restaurants while also scheduling your meals for the entire week...aka doing meal prep, without the cooking and chopping!

The subscription-based meal service lets you choose your favorite bites from local eateries and schedule deliveries up to 1 week in advance. And at a 40% discount, each meal only costs $6.99! Club Feast makes restaurant delivery more efficient at every step -- from allowing restaurants to make use of their kitchens in off-peak hours to minimizing their carbon footprint by optimizing delivery routes.

And if you change your mind, no worries, you can make any changes to your order until 6pm the night before.

Head to the link in our bio to sign up for free and use our code SECRET to get $20 off your first few meals! Let’s feast 😋🍴 #mysecretnyc

@alonglastname's stunning public art pieces can now be seen all over Times Square (and in Lincoln Center). Celebrating the strength, resilience, and diversity of the Asian American and Pacific Islander community, arist Amanda Phingbodhipakkiya addresses confining stereotypes in pop culture as well as the heartbreaking violence that has become increasingly severe during COVID-19 with "We Are More." 🌼
.
The second slide reads: "We are more than your Asian sidekick, the confused foreigner, the future doctor, your submissive plaything, the helpless refugee, the dragon lady, the straight A student, the computer hacker, the martial arts master, the spunky girl with dyed hair, the quiet kid, the dependable worker, the Tiger mom.”
.
📸: @timessquarenyc 
📸: @lincolncenter

Located in Flatiron, this is THE place to visit for superfans of our favorite ’90s show. You’ll be able to hang out on iconic sets — from Rachel and Monica’s apartment to Central Perk (where you can really order coffee!), designed exceptionally down to every last detail — play trivia games, see props and costumes, get an insider look with videos and interviews about the making of the show, and recreate famous scenes like getting Ross’s couch up the stairs (just don’t forget to shout PIVOT!).

Of course, there are countless safety measures in place, like social distancing markers, one-way flow, and “Monica Clean” sanitizing stations. Follow @friendstheexperience & head to the link in our bio to get your tickets now! #mysecretnyc

[LINK IN BIO] Believe it or not, NYC has always been teeming with wildlife (and no, we don't just mean rats & pigeons!). And New Yorkers have found a particular fondness for beautiful birds of all shapes and sizes. We decided to take a look back at some of the city's most famous fowl (aka bird celebrities) New Yorkers just can't get enough of, from the OG obsession (the Mandarin Duck) to the tiny owl rescued from the Rockefeller Christmas Tree this year. 🦆 Suffice it to say, we're "owl in" with owls 😅🦉 Swipe through for some adorable memories & head to the link in our bio for the full history!
📸: @ravensbeardwildlifecenter (#3)
📸: @davidlei (#5)

column4:
[LINK IN BIO] This Nailed It! At-Home bake off challenge will have you making cakes that look like...hamburgers and fries 🍔🍟😍
.
Turns out that everything really is cake! Get tickets to this live Zoom bake-off experience and you’ll get a Nailed It! baking kit delivered to your door with all the ingredients you need to attempt this epic illusion cake challenge, including a can of Baker’s Joy! The original nonstick baking spray with flour takes all the work out of having to grease pans and sheets for baking. Just one quick spray, and you’re good to go – a particularly handy product to have during a timed bake-off...😏
.
Want to bake your fast food favorites out of cake? Whether you nail it or not – it’s a guaranteed good time. Hit the link in bio to get your hands on tickets now! ☝️ #mysecretnyc

column4:
Credit: @nycgo 
.
New Year's Eve in Times Square will look a little different this year. Rather than the enormous crowd, the Crossroads of the World will host fewer than 100 people—all essential workers invited to watch the on-site performances of headliners Gloria Gaynor ("I Will Survive"), Jennifer Lopez, Billy Porter, and Jimmy Allen, which will be broadcast on TV, as the celebration is every year.⁠
⁠
This NYE, however, there will be a new way to view the ball drop at home. As Tim Tompkins, president of the Times Square Alliance, tells @pix11news (link in bio): "There is a New Year’s Eve app, which is interactive. You can even choose the camera angles."⁠
⁠
Pictured here, of course, are this year's NYE numerals. You can see them up close in Times Square through Wednesday (December 23). If you do, be sure to #MaskUpNYC, and give your fellow New Yorkers space so we can #StayWellNYC.⁠
⁠
